    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen using `nvim_buf_set_extmarks` inside a decoration provider with the `ephemeral = true` option, the options `sign_text`, `sign_hl_group`, `line_hl_group`, and `number_hl_group` have no effect.\n\nSetting non-ephemeral extmarks with these properties in a decoration provider works as expected (although those extmarks are not automatically cleared, which is also expected).\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\nvim.opt.statuscolumn = [[%@SignCb@%s%=%T%@NumCb@%l│%T]]\n\nlocal ns = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('scratch')\nvim.api.nvim_set_decoration_provider(ns, {\n  on_win = function(_, _, bufnr)\n    vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(bufnr, ns, 0, 0, {\n      sign_text = '→',\n      sign_hl_group = 'Error',\n      line_hl_group = 'Error',\n      number_hl_group = 'Error',\n      ephemeral = true,\n    })\n  end,\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe decoration options should apply as they normally would, meaning that the sign text and highlighting groups should be rendered accordingly even when ephemeral = true is set (and cleared accordingly).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-2025+gc85d15e0d5\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nFedora 41\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nGhostty 1.1.3-HEAD+95daca61\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuild from repo",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
